<TITLE> Clandestine arms factory found in Maheshkhali </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)--Police have found a clandestine firearms manufacturing facility in the hilly terrain of Cox's Bazaar's Maheshkhali island upazila. Officer in charge of Maheshkhali Police Station Swapan Kumar Nath said the facility was discovered on top of Hoanak hill after information was gleaned from a man arrested with firearms. Sirajul Islam Mostaque was detained with a firearm at 10pm on Thursday from an autorickshaw in Panirchhara, OC Swapan told bdnews24.com "Police went to the plastic-shed manufacturing facility on top of Hoanak hill. Nearly all equipment required for manufacturing firearms were there, except for the lead machine," said the OC. Mostaque had informed the police that four of them used to manufacture arms in that facility and sell them for the last one and a half months. According to Mostaque, a person named Jafar Alam is the ring leader and other two members are Abdur Rashid and Shahid Ullah. Police could not arrest any of the others. Mostaque is from Munshir Dail area of Maheshkhali. bdnews24.
